@node Inst
Put the Re2Te.Config in your sys:s and edit the lines 1,2 and 3
In line number 1 you have to define your @{"cdpath" LINK cdpath}
In line number 2 you have to define your @{"headers" LINK head}
In line number 3 you have to define a path for your custom editor (ed,Ced) 
I propose to create a directory and put there all your cdpaths and headers.
The last four lines define your screen palette if the program uses a @{"Custom Screen" LINK custom} 
There is an example with a Re2Te.config file and a directory called Inet which
contains the cd-path and the header.

Put the font in your sys:fonts directory

Ready.
@endnode


@NODE Prog 
This program loads and recent and generates a file called ".r2t"
The file .r2t contains all the information you need, when you are working
with Inet and recents.

The first way to work with the .r2t-file 
If you use @{b}TERM, © Olaf Barthel@{ub}, then you have to load the .r2t file
in your @{b}packet window@{ub}. Now you can select any line and press return.
If you want you can select every line and press return.

The second way is, to upload the .r2t file as Ascii-file.
Now every line will be executed. You type no word!!

You can save you selected lines choosing "Save selected" when you want to
know what files you downloaded.
@ENDNODE


